  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you forget your User ID and password for your HDFC Forex Card, follow these steps to recover or reset them:\n\n### 1. **Online Recovery (NetBanking Portal or Mobile App):**\n   - Visit the HDFC Bank NetBanking portal or open the HDFC Bank mobile app.\n   - Click on the **\"Forgot User ID / Password\"** option on the login page.\n   - Provide the required details such as your registered mobile number, email ID, or card number.\n   - Verify your identity through an OTP (One-Time Password) sent to your registered mobile number or email.\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to reset your User ID or password.\n\n### 2. **Customer Care Assistance:**\n   - Contact HDFC Bank\u2019s customer care at **1800 267 6161** (toll-free in India) or **+91 22 3075 6161** (for international calls).\n   - Provide the necessary details to verify your identity (e.g., card number, registered mobile number, etc.).\n   - Request assistance to recover or reset your User ID and password.\n\n### 3. **Visit the Nearest HDFC Branch:**\n   - Visit your nearest HDFC Bank branch with your Forex Card and a valid ID proof.\n   - Inform the bank representative about your issue, and they will guide you through the recovery process.\n\n### 4. **Self-Registration (if not already registered):**\n   - If you haven\u2019t registered for online access, visit the HDFC Forex Card portal and click on **\"Self Registration\"**.\n   - Follow the steps to register and create a new User ID and password.\n\n### Tips:\n   - Ensure your registered mobile number and email ID are active to receive OTPs and updates.\n   - Always keep your User ID and password secure to avoid future issues.\n\nIf you face any issues, HDFC Bank\u2019s customer care is available 24/7 to assist you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
